    <h4 class="h3">I eat out a lot and don’t have any control over how much salt the chef uses!</h4>

    <p>It is true that you don’t know how much salt is used during cooking at a restaurant — until you ask! Most restaurant chefs will omit salt when requested. You can also do your homework by looking at a restaurant’s website, which should list the sodium content of each dish.</p>

